# Quality Bar — Keep It Production-Grade

This is a platform-quality boilerplate on one Cloudflare Worker. New code must
match the existing bar, not regress it. Full guide: `AGENTS.md` (root). Match the
nearest sibling file over personal preference.

## Definition of Done (every feature)
- Zod-validated input (bounded arrays/strings) → `sanitizeObject()` → DB write.
- Auth enforced (`requireAuth()` on the domain) + **org-scoped** for org-owned data; null-guard every DB result.
- `logAudit()` on mutations (`void logAudit(...)`) with request context (`c.get("requestId")`, `cf-connecting-ip`, `user-agent`); the app-level `auditFlush()` middleware drains detached writes after each request.
- Multi-step writes in `db.transaction()` (needs the `neon-serverless` driver — `neon-http` can't do transactions); errors via `Errors.*` / `GraphQLError` only.
- Endpoint added in `src/node/routes/{domain}.ts`; new domains mounted in `routes/index.ts` (auth applied there). Scheduled work registered in `cron.ts` + `wrangler.toml [triggers]`.
- New secrets registered in `.dev.vars.example`; new bindings typed in `worker.ts` `WorkerBindings` and declared in `wrangler.toml`.
- `pnpm check` passes (Biome + tsc + Vitest) before commit.

## Non-negotiables
- No try-catch in route handlers — `app.ts` `onError` handles errors.
- Drizzle only (no raw SQL); `ACTIVE` filter on all membership queries.
- Auth only from `requireAuth()` (`c.get("claims")`) — never re-parse JWTs in handlers.
- DB lifecycle per-request: `await getDb()`; never cache pools/clients at module scope.
- Secrets via wrangler (`.dev.vars` local, `wrangler secret` deployed); never plaintext credentials.

## Scaling patterns to replicate
- **Idempotency:** `withIdempotency()` for non-idempotent REST mutations (atomic upsert, never SELECT-then-INSERT) — see `routes/users.ts`.
- **N+1:** use `context.loaders.*` (DataLoader) in GraphQL field resolvers.
- **Async/scheduled work:** Cloudflare Cron Triggers (`cron.ts` + `wrangler.toml [triggers]`); job bodies MUST throw on failure (a swallowed error records a false success — there is no DLQ).
- **Recursive utils:** depth-bound them (mirror `redactSensitive`).
- **Audit rows are immutable** (DB rejects UPDATE / in-window DELETE) — never put secrets in `metadata`.
- **Workers limits:** 128MB isolate memory + CPU-time caps; push heavy media/batch work to a cron job (or future Queues), not the request path.

## Don't
- Don't hand-roll a `Response`/`{ statusCode, body }`, skip sanitize, `await` audit on the hot path,
  cache a DB pool at module scope, or re-add AWS-era toggles (`ORIGIN_VERIFY_SECRET`, `ENABLE_WAF`).
